"reasoning": [
"1. An injured employee is generally required to submit to an employer-requested medical examination at reasonable times under the statute.",
"2. However, the employer’s right to compel an examination is not absolute and must be exercised reasonably in light of the surrounding circumstances.",
"3. The authorized treating physician referred the employee to a specific orthopedic specialist on July 3, 2024, triggering the employer’s statutory duty to approve the referral or provide a panel of alternatives within three business days.",
